        <a class="anchor" id="kaysersberg"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Kayserberg-Vignoble, France</h2>
        <p>Northwest of Colmar is the colorful medieval town of Kaysersberg-Vignoble, another charming place to explore on foot. Some of the town's most scenic areas include the half-timbered houses around the <strong>Fontaine Constantin</strong> fountain, as well as the houses lining the river which you can view from the <strong>Pont Fortifie</strong> bridge. Be sure to also explore the area around the bridge to see more lovely medieval homes.</p>
        <p>You can take a short hike from town up to the ruins of the 13th century <strong>Castle of Kaysersberg</strong>, which hosts fantastic views overlooking the town as well as a dungeon.</p>
    </section>



